<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Focus on visuals]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2493&amp;p=12258#p12258"><![CDATA[
The Winaero 2.0 skin was created specifically to match the Start Menu Glass color with the Taskbar. I think it's a close match, it's a lot more transparent than the default skin but it tries to preserve readability by not being the same level of transparency as the Taskbar. In fact when I tried Start8 and StartIsBack on Windows 8.1 and the taskbar/glass color was a light shade, it was hard to read the text on the Taskbar as well as the Menu.<br /><br />Also take a look at this topic: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=1186&amp;p=6210">http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewt ... 186&amp;p=6210</a><!-- m --> You might be able to tweak the colors easily with the table of values.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Apr 17, 2014 10:39 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
