<div class="quotetitle">Ivo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Are you saying that this doesn't look like an exact replica of the start menu in Windows 7 utilizing the Windows 8 Visual Style? <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/Classic-Shell-4/win7">http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/Cla ... ell-4/win7</a><!-- m --><br /></div><br /><br />The Start Menu does not have a look that is <em>native</em> to the taskbar. With SIB or Start 8 you get the feel that the Start Menu and the taskbar are made of the same material texture. Classic Shell looks like a band-aid.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">GauravK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />The Start Menu supports skins and you can make your own skins. I made a skin to make it match the transparent taskbar better in Windows 8.1: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://winaero.com/blog/get-the-best-looking-start-menu-for-classic-shell-4-with-winaero-skin-2-0/">http://winaero.com/blog/get-the-best-lo ... -skin-2-0/</a><!-- m --><br /></div><br /><br />I tried that skin but I kept getting a blackish shade in the Start Menu whereas the taskbar looks less dark<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">JohnBurns wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Why don't you just find and use something that suits your tastes? Or, better yet make one. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_idea.gif" alt=":idea:" title="Idea" /> <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/Classic-Shell-4/win7">http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/Cla ... ell-4/win7</a><!-- m --><br /></div><br /><br />If I knew how to I would make one. I fiddled with the glass color but can't get the same level of transparency as the taskbar. Not to take away anything from Classic Shell's quality but visuals make people want to use the product.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3523">WinOSXBuntu</